    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-02-09T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-02-09T11:00:00-05:00" n="971"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d971">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.41B1/68: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-02-09T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 9, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 9—12:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Department’s circular January 29, 3 p.m., to Paris. Doctor Schacht<note n="6"
                        xml:id="d971fn6">Hjalmar Schacht, German Minister for Economic Affairs, and
                        President of the Reichsbank.</note> told me Germany ought to accept and that
                    he would be glad to go himself. Von Neurath<note n="7" xml:id="d971fn7"
                        >Constantin von Neurath, German Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> said
                    about the same to me on February 3 and added that he would talk with Schacht and
                    others and let us know their decision. No reply has come yet. I have my doubts
                    about any participation useful as it might be.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodd</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
